<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 6:23PM MDT  by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Weld
County through 715 PM MDT...
At 623 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northeast of Pawnee Buttes, or 24 miles south of Kimball,
moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas near the northeast
corner of Weld County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
